items.name: Archaeopteryx X Raptor
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Nanogryphus</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">almost as identical to an Archaeopteryx but shouldn't be mixed up with one. This large raptor has the ability to be as good on ground as in the air.</>

items.name: Ankylosaurus X Doedicurus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Ankylodicurus</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">The Ankylodicurus is a compact hybrid with osteoderms covering 80% of its mass, making it very armored, not to mention its intimidating spikes which could be dangerous to anything trying to eat it. Thanks to the Doedicurus cross, it can roll at high speeds and can also work like a mobile mortar and pestle.</>

items.name: Ankylosaurus X Yutyrannus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Calliorex</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This hybrid resembles more of a hairy lizard than a hybrid. It has a some sort of alpha effect around other creatures and it can make other target one specific creature and kill it with the help of the wild.</>
Resistant against: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Yutyrannus fear</>

items.name: Archaeopteryx X Gallimimus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Bellucercolestes </>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1"> It is almost as fast as a Gallimimus, agile and lightweight as an Archaeopteryx, may be one of the strongest of the Type 4 hybrids.</>
Resistant against: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">N/A</>

items.name: Argentavis X Magmasaur X Phoenix
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Vulcanotavis</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This bird can use its naturally burning wings to bring hell to anything coming close to it.</>

items.name: Argentavis X Tapejara
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Argentjara </>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">A flying hybrid that has the body of an Argentavis but the wings and agile movement of the Tapejara. </>

items.name: Titanoboa X Argentavis
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Serpentmoloch</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</> /<RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1"> Basically a flying snake that can with its streamlined body dive and gain a lot of speed upon diving, similar to that of a griffin.</>
Resistant against: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">N/A</>

items.name: Baryonyx X Reaper
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Baryxenox</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This hybrid could be simply descibed as a more agile Reaper king. Utilizing the Baryonyx' swim speed and its more agile build, this makes it a versatile hunter, it is also naturally immune to radiation.</>

items.name: Basilisk X Magmasaur
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Cherufelisk</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1">Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">The Cherufelisk has the ability to gas and ignite its prey. Like a Basilisk it can burrow underground, but can also mine metal nodes and smelt them inside of the hot Cherufelisk.</>

items.name: Beaver X Rock Golem
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1"> Lithocastor</> 
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">A rather peculiar hybrid that is covered by some sort of rocky osteoderms. This hybrid can use its powerful jaw to not only take down trees, but also giant boulders.</>
Resistant against: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Fire, bleed</>

items.name: Giant Bee X Dire Bear
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Ursabee</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This hybrid is basically just a flying bear. Thanks to its incredible mimicry, it can easily access honey via wild beehives, it also asexually produces regular bee larvae and can send out giant bees when feeling threatened. Observation suggests that the bees are connected to the ''Bear'' as a Hive mind, thus can be controlled.</>
Resistant against: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Bees</>

items.name: Kaprosuchus X Lamprey X Arthropluera
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Blood Gorge</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1">Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">The Blood Gorge earned its nickname for its hyper-aggressive nature. While it acts like a predator, it usually tries to keep its prey alive to parasitically feed on them for long periods of time.</>

items.name: Titanoboa X Compy X Pegomastax
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Agilioboa</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Support Pet</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">A quadrupedal snake with fibers covering its back. Despite its frail and primitive body type, it has the capacity to carry a human, and could potentially be used as a carriable mount.</>

items.name: Titanoboa X Diplodocus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Neoboaspondylus</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">A very unique hybrid that looks like a dinosaur, but is actually a giant snake with legs. Neoboaspondylus can be used to inflict torpor to large creatures which is a cheaper way to use it to tame creatures with.</>
Resistant against: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">N/A</>

items.name: Scorpion X Therizinosaurus X Leech
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Gymnopelix </>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">A large bipedal scorpion with the head of a leech and body of a Therizinosaurus. This hybrid lives in a symbiosis with 'leech flea' like crossbreeds that seemingly live under an hour, they are used to do collateral DoT on a creature that the Gymnopelix bit. </>

items.name: Carnotaurus X Electrophorus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Fosotaurus</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">A very dangerous hybrid that shares the electric abilities from an eel, the other half of it makes this large monster more reactive than any other large carnivorous hybrid. </>

items.name: Chalicotherium X Megaloceros X Therizinosaurus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Supertherium</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>/<RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This hybrid has dna from three different herbivorous creatures.It has the ability to hurl giant rocks several hundred meters and efficently harvest wood.</>

items.name: Hyaenodon X Dire Bear
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Ursadon</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This incredibly vicious hypercarnivore that usually goes by Chemosit or the Nandi Bear possesses the strength and resiliance of a Dire Bear, and the speed of the Hyaenodon. The Hyaenodon genes have shown to be more dominant than the Dire Bear's thus making these hybrids incredibly social but gruesome pack hunters.</>

items.name: Allosaurus X Daeodon
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Trichodosaura</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">A large hungry Dinosaur that can heal its allies, this hybrid has the strength of an Allosaurus while it has the healing abilities of a Daeodon.</>

items.name: Daeodon X Mammoth X Woolly Rhino
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Lurduops </>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>/<RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">A giant mammal with an incredibly strong head, neck and appetite. Its healing radius is 4x larger than a Daeodon's </>

items.name: Rex X Pachyrhino X Phoenix
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Diablotaurus</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">An extremely strong hybrid that strangely resembles a xenomorph. It's immune system is so unstable that it has some way found a way to passively create potassium chloride, which when mixed with its fiery breath creates a purple flame.</>

items.name: Dimetrodon X Dilophosaur X Ankylosaurus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Dilophorhinotyrannus </>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>/<RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This hybrid can use its heavy tail to harvest metal and rocks and heavily damage stuff, its acidic spit also gives it a great advantage in range.</>

items.name: Dimetrodon X Megalosaurus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Dimetrosaurus </>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a unique hybrid which has artificial synapsid dna that acts like sort of a drug which makes the hybrid more vulnerable to damage but will always make it hyper-active.</>

items.name: Diplocaulus X Sarcosuchus
items.description: Create a Diplocaulus X Sarcosuchus hybrid, this will let you have a hybrid called Sarcocaucalus, a vicious Crocodilian with the body smooth as a salamanders which imporves this monster's swimming speed, the smooth body also releases bubbles for you to breathe in to.

items.name: Dodo X Parasaur X Featherlight
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Avidodo </>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Pet</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Basically a flying dodo with bioluminescence, it is seen as one of the most beautiful flying hybrids out there and with its more advanced senses, it can detect more things.</>

items.name: Dodo X Vulture
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Dodoinfernum </>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1">Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This is literally a dodo from hell. These hybrids can't fly and rely on flapping its wings like the terror bird when it's gliding. The Dodoinfernum's gut is very dry and corossive, and could be used as a meat spoiler.</>
Resistance:<RichColor Color="1,1,1">N/A </>

items.name: Doedicurus X Brontosaurus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Pachycantorus </>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a sauropod with impenetrable armor. The tip of its tail is so heavy and devastating that it can destroy metal structures. It is a great stone harvester.</>

items.name: Arthropluera X Meganeura
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Arthrofly </>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a dragonfly-like insect that produces high amount of acid that somewhat resembles of giant corrossive peas. This hybrid likes to rest on others and due to its high carry weight, you can ride it.</>

items.name: Dung Beetle X Phiomia
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Haploscarab</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a large armored beetle with the only part not being part exoskeleton, the jaw. This beetle lacks a cloaca and spits its feces instead, might seem revolting but it makes its feces comparable to fertilizer quality.</>

items.name: Ichthyosaurus X Dunkleosteus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Kritopeltosaurus </> 
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">A mammal with seering bone teeth. This hybrid is very fast for its size and has thick armor embedded around its head.</>

items.name: Erythroterror Pod
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Erythroterror</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,1">Rogue</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Erythroterror live their lives in pain. They prey on some creatures solely for their blood and have been observed vomiting that old blood-mixed-acid as a form of defense. This abomination also has a hatred for its prey and simply destroys environments purely out of spite. Termination is a priority, where they come from does not matter to you, no further questions. Ctrl, Q </>

items.name: Ravager X Magmasaur
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Canisinfernum</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a large bloodthirsty dog with magma infused claws. The ravager genes with its indtimidating looks makes this hybrid untouched by large carnivores.</>

items.name: Equus X Hyaenodon
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Equicrut</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a horse like hybrid with hyaena type features. It is a ferocious omnviore and can regenerate most of its health by eating carcasses, like the Hyaenodon, it grows stronger in packs. Spicing the hybrid with some equus features and you get one of the fastest travel mounts.</>

items.name: Tyrannosaurus X Spinosaurus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Kaiserspinotyrannus</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a very vicious carnivore that is both quick in the water and on land. The large snout from the spinosaurus and the biteforce from the rex makes this hybrid not only effective for fishing but also reach its enemies a little bit more and crushing them.</>

items.name: Stegosaurus X Kentrosaurus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Titanocercosaurus</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a Stegosaurid with exaggerated tail spikes that can penetrate stone structure with ease.</>

items.name: Pulmonoscorpius X Eurypterid
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Thalassoscorpius </>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a super-''scorpion'' that is not only faster than a regular pulmoscorpius, but almost as strong as a Tyrannosaurus rex. It has a non-lethal venom which is used to paralyze its victims. </>

items.name: Liopleurodon X Leedsychthis
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Thalassodraco</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>/<RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a giant whale-like fish that has teeth the size of a person. This hybrid produces high decibels that can exceed up to 160 decibels making anything in its proximity paralyzed for a limited time. It can also breach out of the water to catch prey 30 meters above the surface. </>

items.name: Coelacanth X Thorny Dragon X Carno
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Lutodraco </>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">A rather peculiar hybrid that was intended to test the versatile Coelacanth genes. This muddy hybrid is an opportunistic hunter that uses the Thorny Dragon scales as a rattle to intimidate other creatures.</>

items.name: Trike X Lystro
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Microceratops</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Pet </>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">The sole purpose of this hybrid was to genetically engineer Triceratops babies to stay young their entire lives. The Lystrosaurus dna boosts its metabolism just for this purpose.</>

items.name: Giganotosaurus X Stego X Sarcosuchus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Macrocercodraco</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>/<RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a giant carnivore with stegosaurus plates. This hybrid might not show much crocodilian resemblence, but its faster swimming speed and longer attack range it is fairly noticable that it is more of a versatile raid hybrid.</>

items.name: Magmasaur X Fire Wyvern X Rock Drake
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Magsuredrake</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0"> Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">The Magsuredrake is incredibly powerful. Its fire breath contains traces of oil which makes it work like a giant flame thrower. Wars waged with this hybrid have made villages into charcoal.</>

items.name: Managarmr X Direwolf
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Frostvarg </>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a cold and very active wolf. The DNA from the Managarmr made this hybrid get element enhanced abilites, one of these abilities are that it constantly makes the water vapour around it to ice, which in return can be used as a defense to fire elemental creatures.</>

items.name: Manta X Ammonite
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Mantammonite</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">The Mantammonite uses its shell as protection against the blistering sun, as well as helping it to produce methane that it uses to lift off the gound with. The problem is that it takes a toll on the Mantammonite's stamina to fly, but fortunately gets the energy and methane back when idling in the air.</>

items.name: Mantis X Megalosaurus X Trilobite
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Mantissaur</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This hybrid has an odd selection of combinations, utilizing creatures that have no close link to one another. It has a thick layer of exoskeleton and with the help from its pack members, they can send out healing frequencies, boosting their metabolism while making their complex insect brain think a little faster.</>

items.name: Tyrannosaurus X Microraptor
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Dracoavirannus</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">the bones from the microraptor makes this hybrid have hollow bones which makes this Tyrannosaurid very fast for its size. With the Rex' biteforce and the Microraptors cunning abilities, this is one of the most dangerous hybrids.</>

items.name: Kaprosuchus X Lymantria
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Phalainasuchus</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">A insect like reptile with wings big enough to lift the light body off the ground. </>

items.name: Phiomia X Moschops
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Phiomiaops</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Food</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This synapsid has the ability regrow parts of its body where it isn't necessary. While this isn't something you would charge in battle with, it is something you would grab a bite from without hurting it. If it enjoys being harvested from, that's up to you to judge.</>

items.name: Mosasaurus X Carbonemys
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Sarcochelys</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>/<RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a giant armored mosasaurus that blends one of the islands most protected creatures and the top predator of the oceans. </>

items.name: Lymantria X Otter X Ovis
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Caelumlator</> 
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">A huge moth hybrid which genetics are so manipulated and changed that it makes this moth a surprising ruler of the sky. It can use its giant wings to push back larger creatures and with its almost streamlined body, it can dive to gain speed and momentum.</>

items.name: Reaper X Megalania X Thorny Dragon
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Reaperothorax</> 
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">A very dangerous super lizard that luckily can't scale walls like its Megalania parent. This hybrid is very cunning and hold on-</>

items.name: Operation Obelisk
items.description:
<RichColor Color="1,0,0,1">CRAFTING THIS WILL UNLEASH A DESTRUCTIVE ABOMINATION OF ALL BOSSES</>
Operation Obelisk was a failed hybrid operation that was supposed to be used as the ultimate weapon of war, but due to several failures of containing it, the operation finally broke out letting out powerful ear shattering screams. The frequencies of the roars matched the ones that the Dragon lets out. 
One observation confirmed that the roars intensified the closer it got to an obelisk, some propose that Operation Obelisk siphon the mysterious powers of the Obelisks, hence its name.

items.name: Stormenzmaj Summoner
items.description: What the hell is a Stormenzmaj?

items.name: Cyborg Hybrid Anomaly Boss
items.description: <RichColor Color="1,0,0,1">CRAFTING THIS WILL UNLEASH AN EXTREMELY DANGEROUS BOSS CLASSED HYBRID</> After a couple of rogue scientists thought to themselves, ''Why aspire to create a new ultimate lifeform when you can improve already something that exists?'', Cyber Macrocercodraco or Macrocyberdraco was created. Inteded as a protest against the ones that were going after quantity and finding themselves stuck in a limbo trying to create new genetic perfections, the Cyber Macrocerco became a beacon of telling everyone that the time of cybernetics is here. That didn't last long because after a processor malfunction, the Macrocyberdraco found itself in control again in a newly refined cybernetic body, destroying anything that it didn't see as robotic.

items.name: Operation Banshee
items.description:
Thanks to Calliorex' complex vocal chords and the DNA of several other aggressive herbivorous creatures, creates this super aggressive herbivore that has the mentality of a predator, this hybrid kills because its fun. Operation Banshee can create powerful roars that buff allies and is a great support creature. 
(Ctrl+x will make an alternative buff roar)

items.name: Project Kaiju
items.description:
<RichColor Color="1,0,0,1">CRAFTING THIS WILL UNLEASH A TITAN CLASSED ULTRA HYBRID</>
After finding ourselves on earth, there had to be something to counter Titans, and thus, Project Kaiju was born. Sabotage led this titan classed Ultra hybrid to gain a little more brain than intended, and making this supposed to be controlled sub-titan a wayward and unruly Rogue.

items.name: Strange Anomaly Bait
items.description: ''Among the rubble of the establishment laid secret files, the radiance of the files must have been made from someone hollow, not even a knight would be able to withstand.'' It says that these fibers are made from spoiling something that requires sacrifice <RichColor Color="1,0,0,1">CONSUMING THIS WILL BAIT AN OVERLY DESTRUCTIVE MINI-BOSS</>

items.name: Odd Caelumlator Fibers
items.description: Hmm.. Something tells you to put this inside of a Crossing Table and try to put huge quantities of regular fiber....

items.name: Operation Sapien
items.description: Operation Sapien is one of the most controversial creations as it uses Human DNA to be created. This creature combined with every Raptor-like DNA makes it also one of the most intelligent ones, some scientists says it is sentient and since it contains human DNA in it, it has the will sometimes to kill its creator.

items.name: Operation Urban Fear
items.description: The research table has created the best possible hybrid blueprint. A giant therapod with the combination of Giganotosaurus' rage and Lasiocheloraptor's intelligence. It is calculated that it should be a therapod built carnivore with a pair of feathers on top of its head, presumably used for communication. More information is required about this Operation.

items.name: Otter X Ferox X Trike (Small)
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Lutrinaeparvus </>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Support Pet </>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This hybrid is very closely related to the ferox, the only difference between them is that Lutrinaeparvus cannot transform, so they like being with a larger Ferox species called Lutrinaemagnum</>

items.name: Otter X Ferox X Trike (Large)
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Lutrinaemagnum </> 
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This hybrid is very closely related to the ferox, the only difference between them is that Lutrinaemagnum cannot transform, so they like being with a smaller Ferox species called Lutrinaeparvus</>

items.name: Oviraptor X Gallimimus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Trivoxomimus </>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">an intelligent therapod that can use its well built vocalcords to imitate other creature's sounds.</>

items.name: Pachycephalosaurus X Ovis
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Trachycephalus </>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Unknown </>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a hybrid that is used to harvest mutton from. Trachycephalus is a very passive hybrid, using non-lethal forces to take down predators, but its stupidity can accidentally kill stuff, even itself in the wild.</>

items.name: Pegomastax X Ichthyornis X Microraptor
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Raptoromastax</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Support Pet </>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Being one of the most outrageous hybrids, this little goober boasts (almost) all of the abilities that enhances the stealing ability. Thanks to its even sharper eyes, it can alert players of potential threats and can reveal where they are. They have often been seen playing with their prey before stealing their valuables, dazing them in confusion until it nabs what it sees.</>

items.name: Pegomastax X Baryonyx
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Lasiocheloraptor </>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">this hybrid has several long and sensitive hair that stretches from its snout to its tail, it is mostly used to intimidate larger predators therefore making larger predators neutral towards it. With Baryonyx' cunning hunting abilities and Pegomastax' thieving behaviour, Lasio is able to skin a small creature lightning fast, killing it without even knowing what happened.</>

items.name: Pelagornis X Kaprosuchus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Pelagosuchus </>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Pelasuchus is a curious hybrid that acts like a Pelagornis when it's roaming while being vicious as a Kaprosuchus when hunting. This hybrid has the ability to dive into water and swim, luckily it has extra oily feathers that acts like a protected barrier around every individual feather, allowing it to fly right out of the water. </>

items.name: Plesiosaurus X Angler fish
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Centrodonosaurus </>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">The Centrodonosaurus likes to spend time in the deep. It is incredibly speedy and agile compared to its Plesiosaur brother and even more useful.</>

items.name: Purlovia X Onychonycteris
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Gorgomoloch </>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">this hybrid has skin that stretches from its hind legs to its front legs, and it has unusually strong legs that can lift its body weight 5 times, Thanks to the skin that stretches on its strong legs, this hybrid can jump 15 meters high and glide like a terror bird.</>

items.name: Quetzalcoatlus X Giganotosaurus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Gigadeusopteryx</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Think of a Giga, now think of it with wings. This hybrid was supposed to be dismissed as a failure because of it having 2 extra limbs, rather than having just wings and legs. Be careful as this hybrid still possesses the Giga's rage.</>

items.name: Quetzalcoatlus X Tropeognathus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Tropeocoatlus</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1">Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">The Tropeocoatlus uses its crest to better maneuver in the air, it also gives it the ability to barrel roll. While it has the capacity to do that, we would not recommend barrel rolling while it has a platform saddle equipped. </>

items.name: Dunkleosteus X Carno X Shinehorn X Raptor X Ravager
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Carnoleosteus</> 
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>/<RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This hybrid seems to be liking caves more than the surface biomes, making it a very good caving hybrid thanks to its discretly injected Ravager DNA. Having an unusually high gene variation makes this the only non-operation hybrid that has more than 4 creatures in it.</>

items.name: Rex X Paracer X Gigantopithecus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Gigantotyrannus</> 
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This hybrid is a huge ape-like creature with the head of a Tyrannosaur and the legs of a paracer. It has a layer of thick skin under the fibrous fur and muscles that act as a damage absorbant.</>

items.name: Quetzalcoatlus X Rock Golem
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Colossodraco </>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a giant flying reptile with some sort of rocks as armor that heavily reduces damage of bullets and deflects fire. This hybrid also has the ability to harden its armor, it increases its armor but decreases its speed temporarily. </>

items.name: Sabertooth Tiger X Kaprosuchus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Torvosuchus</> 
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">this hybrid combines the two creatures with strong legs and powerful jaws.</>

items.name: Sarco X Triceratops X Diplocaulus X Kentro
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Tricerasuchus</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This hybrid is very invasive and due to its resiliance and destructive foraging behavior, it has been observed outcompeting several species in the swamps while destroying the ecosystem. The Tricerasuchus was made as a versatile mount and has millions of pores covering its back, making it press out oxygen on command.</>

items.name: Ichthyornis X Jerboa
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Eulestes</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Pet </>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a small mammal-like hybrid with a beak and feathers. This hybrid gives creatures, like the lystrosaurus, a slight XP boost around it.</>

items.name: Basilisk X Reaper X Eel
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Leviathanconstrictor </>.
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a huge sea serpent hybrid that is very agile for its size. It can electrify its targets by making its body a giant electrical cord.</>

items.name: Ovis X Penguin
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Peep</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Unknown</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">A mammal-like bird that is harvested for its polymer-infused meat. It has the ability to passively make organic polymer without having the need to kill them.</>

items.name: Araneo X Mesopithecus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Aracnopithecus</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a literal spider monkey. It's a perfect travelling mount and a really good hybrid to sense anything around it.</>

items.name: Achatina X Carbonemys
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Achatinonemys </>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,0"> Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1"> This hybrid is used as a robust and more resourceful farm creature. It has the ability to create cementing paste and organic polymer, but it has an increased organic polymer yield than a regular Achatina.</>

items.name: Araneo X Achatina
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Araneoacnus</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">this hybrid is, as you would expect with a snail and spider dna, a large spider with a thick exoskeleton. It can spray slimeballs which slow down and kill creatures.</>

items.name: Baryonyx X Spino X Cnidaria X Diploc
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Spinocnidaryx</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1">Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This Spinosaurid shocks its prey and can easily mutalite its competition. Its electric nature makes it incredibly quick for its size.</>

items.name: Bronto X Kentro X Terror Bird
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Apatoramfos</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a large and intimidating hybrid with a devastating tail. This singing hybrid can use its sounds to communicate with allies to boost their morality. </>

items.name: Terror bird X Raptor
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Terrorraptor</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">This is considered to be one of the most social creatures ever created and therefore like to work in groups. Its beak along with its teeth can cut through wood with ease making it rather strong for its size.</>

items.name: Therizinosaurus X Spinosaurus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Spinonychus </>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">this hybrid has the giant multi-stance 'hands' of the Spinosaurus and the giant claws of the Therizinosaurus. When attacked by this hybrid, it will feel like several trees just gets slammed on to you.</>

items.name: Megalodon X Thorny Dragon
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Scekrar </>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a relatively spikey shark that use its poison projectiles to take down other sharks.</>

items.name: Bulbdog X Beelzebufo
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Bulzaba</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a giant toad with razor sharp teeth. The Bulzaba seems to have a loving effects around critters, and it uses those produced endorphins to create poison for both XP bonus, and torpor debuffs.</>

items.name: Troodon X Pteranodon
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Pelosornis</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a ferocious dinosaur with a light but devastating beak-like mouth.</>

items.name: Trike X Mammoth X Kentrosaurus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Mammuthusaura</>
Class: <RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>/<RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">A giant mammoth like saurian with large spikes sticking out from its back. The head of this hybrid is one of the most protected ones out there and bullets seem to have no effect on damaging its head.</>

items.name: Coelacanth X Trilobite
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Ploichthy </>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a semi-aquatic fish-arthropod that can jump out of the water to get to higher ground, it can walk on land and breathe air like the trilobite does. This might be one of the weirdest hybrids. </>

items.name: Tropeognathus X Deinonychus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Neoavirhinus</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a large gliding bird-like reptile that uses its small wings to leap and glide for short distances. It has been observed that they have found a way to use complex speech patterns for communication, and they oddly seem to switch alpha roles in the pack.</>

items.name: Ankylosaurus X Carbonemys
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Megaplocanthus</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,0">Tank</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">one of the most armoured herbivores on the Island, due to the Carbonemyses having short and stubby tails, this makes the tail of this hybrid at the same time lightweight and devastating.</>

items.name: Sarcosuchus X Dire Wolf
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Megacanissuchus</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>/<RichColor Color="1,0,0">Ferocious</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">a fast land croc that can enable its thermal vision to spot camoflauged prey.</>

items.name: Woolly Rhino X Pachyrhinosaurus
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Rhynchoceratops</>
Class: <RichColor Color="0,1,1"> Hyper</>
Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">the Pachyrhino DNA makes this hybrid have a stronger neck and armour on its head that makes this hybrid feel less pain when it runs into enemies, which in return also makes it deal more damage.</>

items.name: Fire Wyvern X Poison Wyvern
items.description: Create a Fire Wyvern X Poison Wyvern, this combination creates a Meteor wyvern.

items.name: Poison Wyvern X Lightning Wyvern
items.description:
Create a Poison Wyvern X Lightning Wyvern, this combination creates a Necro wyvern.
<RichColor Color="1,0,0">ONLY WORKS ON SINGLEPLAYER</>

items.name: Fire Wyvern X Lightning Wyvern
items.description:
Create a Fire Wyvern X Lightning Wyvern, this combination creates a Plasma wyvern.
<RichColor Color="1,0,0">ONLY WORKS ON SINGLEPLAYER</>

items.name: Xanthothanatos Pod
items.description:
Name: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">Xanthothanatos</>

Description: <RichColor Color="1,1,1">The origin of the Xanthothanatos is a mystery, no one knows where they come from, the only thing known is of their ravenous hatred of survivors. Its composition is so diverse at that point where it shouldn't be able for it to survive less than an hour. The research table suggests that the Xanthothanatos on the island are made from a number of failed secret experiments and that any known of these Rogue hybrids should be eradicated before they cause any more environmental damage. </>

items.name: Mejamarberry
items.description: A rather weird looking berry that strangely resembles a tomato, but should definitely not be mixed between tomatoes. Bitter, but can be used to make brown dye.

items.name: Mejamarberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Mejamarberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots. This seed is a cross between Mejo- and amarberry

items.name: Amarcoberry
items.description: A sinister looking berry, gives narcotic like effects to consumer and makes them feel nauseaous. Bitter, but can be used to make green dye.

items.name: Amarcoberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Narcoberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots.

items.name: Naranberry
items.description: This berry is unusually good with nullifying blinding projectiles. Very tasty, and can be used to make orange dye.

items.name: Naranberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Naranberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots. This seed is a cross between an Amar- and Tintoberry

items.name: Lavandaberry
items.description: A berry with a beautiful color but bitter taste, very watery and fills almost every meal

items.name: Lavandaberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Lavandaberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots. This seed is a cross between Mejo- and Azulberry

items.name: Abyssoberry
items.description: This black berry is oddly not black, but has actually a pretty dark form of blue. Don't eat it though if you want to stay awake, since this berry seems to give strong narcotic type effects to anything that consumes it. Bitter, but can be used to make blue dye.

items.name: Abyssoberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Abyssoberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots. This seed is a cross between an Azul- and Narcoberry

items.name: Cianberry
items.description: This fairly common white berry can be eaten in a pinch to recover Food, Stamina, and lose Torpidity. It has a faint sweetness to it, and can be used to make light blue dye.

items.name: Cianberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Stimberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots.

items.name: Purpurberry
items.description: A sweet tasty berry that can be used for purple coloring

items.name: Purpurberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Purpurberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots. This seed is a cross between Azul- and Tintoberry

items.name: Crudoberry
items.description: This odd green berry is has a lovely smell but a bitter taste.

items.name: Crudoberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Crudoberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots. This seed is a cross between Azul- and Amarberry

items.name: Bellanova Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Bellanova crop.  Can be planted in Medium or Large Crop Plots. Will passively make cementing paste and oil

items.name: Dynaberry
items.description: A very bitter berry that significantly clears your mind from the effects of narcotics and drastically fills your hunger. Though it creates a toxin which makes the consumer thirsty and a little bit weaker

items.name: Dynaberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Dynaberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots. This seed is a cross between Stim- and Mejoberry

items.name: Mediberry
items.description: This sweet berry can be used as a healing consumable. While not really as good as a healing brew, it still can make you recover from some injuries.

items.name: Mejoberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Mejoberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots.

items.name: Esplendidoberry
items.description: A very bitter tasting berry among survivors, though is very tasty apparently when wild creatures eat it, strangely enough even carnivores enjoy it.

items.name: Esplendidoberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Esplendidoberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots. This seed is a cross between Mejo- and Narcoberry

items.name: Crossing Table
items.description: The crossing table, stupid name by the way, can be used as a workplace where you can cross different plants to make plant hybrids

items.name: Eierberry
items.description: A berry that resembles an egg. It seems to have no taste but has proven to improve coagulation, making this berry remove any bleeding debuffs upon consumption, but makes you thirstier.

items.name: Eierberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Eierberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots. This seed is a cross between a Stim- and Amarberry

items.name: Venosberry
items.description: Consuming this is fatal and should not be messed around with. You can eat it, but only once. Use this berry to insert it to food to poison people.

items.name: Venosberry Seed
items.description: Eat it to gain a tiny amount of nourishment, or plant it to grow your own Venosberry bush.  Can be planted in Small, Medium, or Large Crop Plots.
